Certifications like Security+ and CISSP-ISSAP have relatively lower percentages of respondents who would not recommend them at 6.06% and 9.72% respectively.
There is a significant percentage of respondents who are unsure about recommending certifications like GCIH and CCAK, with percentages at 23.76% and 22.9% respectively.
Certifications like SSCP and CISSP-ISSEP have a moderate percentage of respondents who would recommend them to a colleague at 10.61% and 9.47% respectively.
The certification with the highest percentage of respondents who are unsure about recommending it is CCSK at 26.9%.
